<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I would like to add a method to fetch a unique row by primary key,  like Zend_Db_Table::find() but instead of returning multiple rows the method will return a single row.</p>

<p>Could be named Zend_Db_Table:: fetchRowByPk() or Zend_Db_Table:: findRow()</p>

<p>so instead to do
$album-&gt;fetchRow('id='.$id);
we could do 
$album-&gt;fetchRowByPk($id);
or
$album-&gt;findRow($id);</p>

<p>which  save a bit of tapping and make the code more readable.</p>

<p>What do you think ?</p>

